data.description: Plan of the floor that shows real time occupancy, areas or sensors location
data.title: Floormap

data.description: Your VergeSense score is very low. It means you need to improve your office utilization. Check your detailed usage statistics to see how to waste less!
data.help:
VS score is the most important indicator of your floor performance, calculated for a selected period of time (week/month/year).

It illustrates the general state of the floor on a 1-10 scale. The higher score your floor gets - the better utilized it is as a whole.

VS score is based on a complex algorithm that includes among others: number of people, capacity and average utilization of the building. Moreover, it considers different factors for each type of space, as each type of space has it own specificity (eg. conference rooms generally are utilised in different way than lounge areas).

Tailored to the space level, VS score gives you a quick yet comprehensive insight into your floor performance.

Additional information on VergeSense score can be find on Support page.
data.title: VS Score

data.description: Shows how your space was used on average over selected period of time, juxtaposed with peaks.
data.help:
This chart shows an average percentage utilization of the floor.

It gives you also information on how this general utilization changed in comparison to the previous period.

• Utilization - helps answer the question "How is the space used compared to capacity?"
data.title: What is the average usage of space?

data.description: Shows floor capacity, how many people are in the floor on average and max number of people during the day
data.help:
Capacity - shows total capacity of floor.

Average Person Count - shows an average number of people in the whole floor, calculated for a selected period of time (week/month/year).
It gives you also information on how this general occupancy changed in comparison to the previous period of time.

Peak Person Count - shows a maximal number of people in the whole floor, calculated for a selected period of time (week/month/year).
It gives you also information on how this peak occupancy changed in comparison to the previous period of time.
data.title: Average Person and Peak Count

data.description: Comparison of capacity between space types. Hover over space type to see capacity and average utilization
data.help:
This chart shows a capacity comparison between all types of spaces for a selected period of time (week/month/year).

It offers you a quick insight on how much space is used by each type of space on the floor.
This chart gives you also information of percentage utilization of each type of space.
data.title: Capacity distribution by space type

data.description: Shows comparison of different kinds of spaces on the floor, based on average number of people
data.help:
This chart shows a percentage comparison of distribution between different types of spaces in the whole floor.

It is based on an average number of people in these spaces, calculated for a selected period of time (week/month/year).

This chart offers you a quick insight on which space is the most (or the least) popular one according to the number of people.
It also gives you information on how distribution of each of these spaces changed in comparison to the previous period of time.
data.title: Popularity by space type

data.description: Average and Peak space utilization for days of the week
data.help:
This chart shows an average daily utilization of the floor for a selected period of time (week/month/year).

It displays data per each working day of the week. This chart offers you a quick insight on during which day of the week your floor is utilized most (or least).
It gives you also information on how utilization for each day of the week changed in comparison to the previous period of time.
data.title: What are the busiest days of the week?

data.description: Shows the comparison of average occupancy vs utilization for each space, for the selected period of time. Click on a space for more detail
data.help:
This chart compares Occupancy and Utilization rates for each space easily identify which spaces need improvement.

• Utilization - helps answer the question "How is the space utilized compared to its capacity"

• Occupancy - helps answer the question "How often is the space used?"

I - over-utilized and under-occupied

II - over-utilized and over-occupied

III - under-utilized and over-occupied

IV - under-utilized and under-occupied
data.title: How do your spaces compare?

data.description: Shows information about average spaces utilization throughout a week/day, over selected period. Utilization - helps answer the question "Are my spaces being used to capacity?
data.help:
This chart highlights how your space is used over the hours of the average work day or work week. The chart shows an average percentage utilization of the floor for each working hours in a selected period. You can analyze an average for a week or a single day. It displays data only for working days and hours.

• Utilization - helps answer the question "Are my spaces being used to capacity?
data.title: How is your space used during an average day?

data.description: Linear chart shows utilization for each day in selected period.
data.help:
By this chart, you can see how usage changes over time. This chart shows the average percentage utilization in your floor for each day in a selected period. You can filter data hourly/daily/weekly/monthly. The view will switch automatically based on the selected period: for a day data are presented hourly, for a week - daily, for a month - weekly, for a period longer than three months - monthly. It displays data only for working days and hours.

• Utilization - is a number of people in selected spaces divided by the capacity of these spaces.
data.title: How is your usage trending over time?

data.description: Linear stacked chart showing average number of people in specific spaces over selected period
data.help:
This chart shows a comparison of average number of people between all types of spaces in your building for a selected period of time (week/month/year).

It displays data only for working days and hours.
You can filter data hourly/daily/weekly/monthly.
View will switch automatically based on selected time period: for a day data is presented hourly, for week - daily, for month - weekly, for a period longer than 3 months - monthly.

This chart offers you a quick insight on how which type of space is utilized in comparison to others.
data.title: Average Number of People
